When defining the `CompositeType`s in our models, we need to call `register_composites`. We are using the sqlalchemy events to do that automatically.

The problem is that when we create our tables automatically through this same code, `register_composites` fails when the types are not created yet.

```
from sqlalchemy_utils.types.pg_composite import register_psycopg2_composite, registered_composites, register_composites

@event.listens_for(Engine, 'engine_connect')
def receive_engine_connect(conn, branch):
#    register_composites(conn)
    for name, composite in registered_composites.items():
        if conn.dialect.has_type(conn, composite.name, schema=composite.schema):
            register_psycopg2_composite(conn.connection.connection, composite)
```

I believe a `checkfirst` flag would be useful for such a case (e.g. `register_composites(conn, checkfirst=True)`), similar to the flags available in the create/drop family of methods.

